original: Lindström, Einar Carl Gustaf, bitr. förste provinsialläkare, Jönköping, f. 5/9/94 i Nättraby, Blek. 1., av stat:-hisp. C. F. Lindström o. Rosa Andersson. G. 27 m. Gunhild Bäckström. Barn: Carl Gustaf f. 29, Gudrun 31, Berit 35, Jan 40, — Stud:ex. i Karlskr. 12, med. kand. 16 o. med. lic. 21 i Lund. E. läk. v. Lunds hosp. o. asyl 18, und :läk. v. Loka brunn 19, bad-läk. v. Götarps brunn 20, marinläk:-stip. 22-23, kommend. s. div:- o. flot-tiljläk., und :läk. v. Målilla san. 22-25, assist :läk. o. tf. und :iäk. v. Malmö allm. sjukh. kir. avd. 25, tf. prov :läk. i Gäddede distr. 25-26, prov:läk. i Vit-tangi distr. 26-29, i Fellingsbro distr. 30-43 o. i Jönköp. distr. sed. 43, bitr. förste prov:läk. i Jönköp. J. sed. 44.
translated: Lindström, Einar Carl Gustaf, assistant senior county medical officer, Jönköping, born on 5/9/94 in Nättraby, Blekinge county, son of civil servant C. F. Lindström and Rosa Andersson. Married on the 27th with Gunhild Bäckström. Children: Carl Gustaf born in 1929, Gudrun in 1931, Berit in 1935, Jan in 1940. Completed high school exams in Karlskrona in 1912, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1916 and a medical licentiate degree in 1921 in Lund. Worked as a medical intern at Lund Hospital and Asylum in 1918, assistant doctor at Loka Spa in 1919, bath doctor at Göta Spa in 1920, maritime medical scholarship recipient from 1922-1923, appointed as a commanding and fleet surgeon, assistant doctor at Målilla Sanatorium from 1922-1925, assistant doctor and temporary senior assistant doctor at Malmö General Hospital Surgical Department in 1925, acting county medical officer in Gäddede district from 1925-1926, county medical officer in Vittangi district from 1926-1929, in Fellingsbro district from 1930-1943, and in Jönköping district since 1943. Assistant senior county medical officer in Jönköping since 1944.
